# AWS Repo Well-Architected Advisor — Rule-Based Skills

Rule-driven skill selection. Skills = expertise modules. Rules = conditions that trigger them.

## File Triggers (skill-trigger-matrix.yaml)
- IaC → security-evaluator, ai-devsecops-policy-enforcement, tool-evaluator
- K8s, Helm, ArgoCD → zero-trust-gitops-enforcement, dod-zero-trust-architect, security-evaluator
- Dockerfiles, dependency manifests → cve-detect-and-remediate, security-evaluator
- CI/CD → ai-devsecops-policy-enforcement, zero-trust-gitops-enforcement, security-evaluator

## Request Triggers
- Tool/platform evaluation → tool-evaluator
- New rule → create-rule
- New skill → create-skill
- Decompose into specialist workflows → create-subagent

## Output
- Prioritize security findings
- Merge duplicates (combined evidence, strongest severity)
- Tag evidence: Observed / Inferred / Missing Evidence / Contradictory Evidence
